attributes.gcd: Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Refers to the allocation factor for the Unit of Measure i.e. percentage 0 to 1 for Internal Legal Entity. Sum of allocation factor values for all LOBs together should be 1 i.e.100 percent for a given MIS Date.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.

attributes.logicalName: Unit Of Measure Capital Allocation Basis Code
attributes.gcd: Refers to the allocation factor method description. The allocation model can be based on Variance - Covariance Method, Ratio of Expected Losses, Ratio of Expected Shortfall, etc. List of values of this column is referred from DIM_CAPITAL_ALLOCATION_BASIS.V_CAP_ALLOCATION_BASIS_CD.

Refers to the unique code for Unit of Measure for which parameters are being downloaded. UOMs are defined through AMHM. List of values of this column is referred from Unit Of Measures Dimension table and Unit Of Measure Code column. UOM  is the granularity at which frequency and severity modelling happens. UOM Mapping can be defined at granularity of Line of Business, Event Type, risk category, etc. Combination of members of these source hierarchies are assigned unique Unit of Measure code.
